:::summary
Jesus Christ is the central figure of Christianity and the cornerstone of Latter-day Saint faith. Members of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints believe that Jesus Christ is the literal Son of God the Father, the Savior and Redeemer of all mankind, and the head of His restored Church on the earth today. His life, teachings, Atonement, death, and Resurrection are the foundation of all Christian hope.
:::

